Marie Diouf has built a businwss from salt flats she saved up to buy, in a trade where most marsh owners are men. Starting off as a harvester, she wondered why the women doing this job never got to keep the proceeds of their work. Nicknamed the "Salt Queen, she now employs between 10 and 20 men and women. Deadly floods sweep through Mali Deadly floods ravage Mali, with the capital Bamako hit hard. Flooding is common in West African nation, located in the semi-desert Sahel region.